adian novelist carol shields giardini is licensed to practice law in both ontario and british columbia as a journalist giardini has contributed to the national post as a columnist she lives in vancouver british columbia with her husband of more than  years and their three children she has written two novels the sad truth about happiness  and advice for italian boys  both published by harpercollins she is currently serving as the th chancellor of simon fraser university since  giardini has been president of weyerhaeuser company limited a subsidiary of weyerhaeuser company in the forestry industry prior to her role as president she joined weyerhaeuser in  and became canadian vicepresident and general counsel in  giardini is an active volunteer and on the board for a number of local vancouver organizations she is a board member for the greater vancouver board of trade chair of the board of the vancouver international writers festival member of the board of directors for univercity at sfu deputy chair of the board of governors at simon fraser university supporter of plan canada volunteer for vancouver ywcas women of distinction awards and young women in business giardini was awarded a queen elizabeth ii diamond jubilee medal in january  for her fundraising efforts for plan canada’s “because i’m a girl” campaign which supports females in tanzania in  giardini was appointed as a officer of the order of canada contents  education  bibliography  awards  notes educationedit giardini in  cambridge university trinity hall — llm law  –  the university of british columbia — llb law  –  simon fraser university — ba economics  –  university of ottawa  université dottawa — economics  –  bibliographyedit the sad truth about happiness harpercollins  advice for italian boys harpercollins  awardsedit shortlisted for the amazonca first novel award  winner of the audie awards  notesedit  giardini named president of weyerhaeuser company limited weyerhaeuser  press release retrieved  febru